  "texts": [
    "Based on what is suggested in the literature, we used 16-second windows with 80% overlap for the MARBLE dataset [4] and 60 seconds windows with 80% overlap for the UCI ADL dataset [39].Considering the supervised baselines, we used the code available in public repositories (Deep-CASASfoot_1 and DeepConvLSTMfoot_2).",
    "We slightly modified the existing implementations to ensure compatibility with our software environment and data structures, while faithfully reproducing the architectures described in the literature.",
    "In all of our baselines, the LSTM layers have 64 units, while for the convolutional block of DeepConvLSTM we used a single convolutional layer with 8 2x2 filters.",
    "Before feeding it to the networks, environmental sensor data is converted into multivariate binary time-series following a standard approach in the literature [46].",
    "4.3.2 Dataset splitting strategy."
  ],
